description: As forewarned by future Trunks, the z-fighters have just finished 3 years of rigorous training to face a new foe. These new villains, the androids have appeared unawares, in a city, and it seems that they are looking for someone. Who is this they want and why?
name: Vegetas Framg√•ng

description: A new android has surfaced, his name is Cell! This one's been synthesized out of every single z-fighter's cell and thus has a vast array of powers. What's more, he's looking to suck androids 17 and 18 into his body to give him supposed invulnerability. Can he be stopped before its too late?
name: Ultrakrigarna

description: Cell is in his perfect form, and almost omnipotent. The z-fighters are powerless before him. Goku believes that Gohan has enough power to defeat Cell. Does this possibility stand or is Cell finally too powerful to be defeated?
name: Den O√∂vervinnelige

description: The z-fighters have been beaten. But still hope is left. Somehow, android 18 has been brought out of Cell's body. Now Cell is about to explode, threatening to endanger everyone's lives. Can Goku hatch a plan in time to save earth?
name: Son-Goku Mot Cell

description: Goku fights Cell, Goku forfeits and chooses Gohan to fight next; everyone is surprised but when he fights everyone is completely amazed but Cell is still much stronger than Gohan. Android 16 tries to beat Cell by using the bomb inside him but realises Bulma took it out and Cell blasts him in half. Then Cell creates 6 Cell Jr.'s and sends them down to beat everyone to get Gohan angry so that he get stronger and then Hercule throws the remains of 16's head infront of Gohan and makes a little speech. Gohan gets really angry and turns super saiajin 2 and starts beating up Cell, Cell gets desparate and self-destructs but Goku teleports him to kaio sama's planet therfore killing himself, Cell and Kaio sama but Cell regenarates and kills Trunks and unleashes a kamehameha at full power and Gohan sends one back also at full power. then while they do that Vegeta sends a blast at Cell to distract him and Gohan beats him! then they use the dragon balls to bring back everyone back to life then Trunks goes back to his time and beats Android17 and 18 and Cell.
name: Tillbaka Till Framtiden

description: Gohan has grown up and has recently assumed a secret identity, Saiyanman. What's more, he has a new baby brother, Goten. Also it seems that he has fallen in love with Vid el, Mr. Satan's daughter. The "World Martial Arts Tournament" is approaching and everyone's training hard.
name: En Ny Hj√§lte

description: The " World Martial Arts Tournament" has started. But a wave of conspiracy is hanging in the air. Two competitors have stolen Gohan's power and fled towards the unknown. The Z-fighters including Goku and Supreme Kai are in hot pirsuit to find out the truth.
name: Krigslist

description: yamuBoo having just absorbed Gohan, fights Goku and Vegeta combined. They have a very big fight but boo absorbs them in the end. They go inside boo and defuse and find everyone else and free them. Boo turns back into his first form. They then free the fat boo. Boo then transforms into kid boo and destroys the Earth but Goku Vegeta, Hercule, dende, teleport to the lord of lords world but boo teleports there too. They start fighting and a huge battle wages. Eventually fat boo comes out of kid boo and starts fighting him while vegeta tells dende to go to new namek to get the namekian dragon balls and vegeta asks him to restore the earth and bring everyone, apart from the evil, back to life. They then try to make a genkidama and get energy from everyone on earth. They then launch the genkidama at kid boo but goku hasn't got enough power so they use the last wish on the dragon balls to give him his power back and defeat boo. At the end he looks in the past and in the future and sees his battles in gt and in the animated movies.
name: Avskedet

description:
Fear the touch of the Grey Gargoyle! His merest graze can turn you to stone, something that Ben Grimm knows a Thing or two about! What will happen when these two gods of granite collide? And where's the rest of the Fantastic Four?

Just when it looks like The Thing has beaten the Grey Gargoyle in their fight, this new foe turns Ben into stone. We can see that the Grey Gargoyle is working together with another foe, a woman later to be revealed as Senso. The missing three members of the FF enter the scene at the end of the story and Mr. Fantastic tells both the Grey Gargoyle and Senso to step away from the Thing.
name: Flesh and Stone

description: No joke: one of the FF's lives is majorly altered in this issue! The Fantastic Four race to rescue one of their own from the clutches of the Grey Gargoyle, but will their efforts be too little, too late? And did we mention that FANTASTIC FOUR is now scripted by Jeph Loeb?!
name: Things Change

description: The Fantastic Four gets trapped in the Negative Zone, but which teammate gets stranded behind? And who are the Nega-Explorers? Plus: after months of scheming, the Gideon Board finally makes their move! ¬†
name: Into the Breach

description: Mr. Fantastic, Invisible Woman and the Thing, ambushed in the Negative Zone! The Human Torch, trapped back on Earth! Hellscout, a new Marvel superstar... but is he here to help or hurt the Fantastic Four?¬†
name: Marooned

description: Guest-penciler Stuart Immonen stops by, as the Human Torch renews his famous feud with Namor! The Thing, Mr. Fantastic and Invisible Woman are trapped in the Negative Zone! Meanwhile, back on Earth, Johnny Storm has to face an enraged Sub-Mariner! Maybe Namorita, Ant-Man and She-Hulk can help!¬†
name: A Clear & Present Danger

description: With Mr. Fantastic, Invisible Woman and The Thing marooned in the Negative Zone, Johnny Storm forms a new FF! His goal: to take the battle to the Gideon Board in an effort to rescue his family! His problem: the Gideon Board has most of Reed Richards' technology... and will use it to stop intruders! So who joins the Torch's team? It's all revealed here!¬†
name: And the Walls Came Thumbling Down

description: The FF, Hellscout, Annihilus and the Nega-Explorers collide in the fiery finale of the Negative Zone epic! What, you want more? Sheesh! Okay, howzabout Namorita, Ant-Man and She-Hulk? ¬†
name: Annihilation!

description: In the aftermath of the Negative Zone saga, one member of the FF has been radically changed! You'll see a new costume and a new identity for one of our intrepid explorers, but we can't reveal who it is or how the changes happened! All we can say is if you've ever been even a casual fan of the Fantastic Four, you'll want to read this!¬†
name: Thou Can't Get There From Here

description: Continued from FANTASTIC FOUR 2001, it's part two of the epic Abraxas Saga! One step closer to Armageddon, the FF hunt for clues to one of the most dangerous cosmic beings they've ever encountered! But what threat is so dire that it requires the assistance of cosmic crusaders such as the Silver Surfer, Captain Marvel and Adam Warlock?¬†
name: It's Too Late To Stop Now!

description: Abraxas has come to New York City, but the FF is racing through alternate Earths! Mr. Fantastic, the Thing and the Invisible Woman hurtle through dimensions on a desperate quest, but will they find the only weapon that can destroy Abraxas... or will the Atlantean Empire and the Challengers of Doom prove their undoing?¬†
name: Just Imagine...

first_appearance_teams.name: Doc Fantastic and his Five for the Future

team_credits.name: Doc Fantastic and his Five for the Future

description: The Abraxas Saga continues, even as the goliath introduced in FANTASTIC FOUR 2001 hunts the FF through the Multiverse! Last issue the Fantastic Four was sent on a quest through the Multiverse to find elements of the Ultimate Nullifier. In issue #48, they... well, we're not telling, since that'd ruin the surprise that leads up to issue #49's stunning conclusion! Suffice it to say, this sci-fi extravaganza continues to build as the FF struggle to defeat a villain on a par with Galactus!¬†
name: World's Apart

first_appearance_teams.name: Doc Fantastic and his Five for the Future

team_credits.name: Doc Fantastic and his Five for the Future

description: Having collected the Ultimate Nullifier and confronted Abraxas, who stands poised to destroy the Multiverse, the Fantastic Four fear it's all for naught. With the end of time near, they turn at last to the one force capable of confronting this ultimate evil... but you'll have to buy this comic to find out what that force is!¬†
name: Dark Victory

description: A team of titanic talents celebrate the FF's 50th issue with a 64-page extravaganza! 4 new stories for the Fantastic Four! In our first fabulous tale -- which is also a 'Nuff Said story -- the team of writers Carlos Pacheco and Rafael Marin and penciler Tom Grummett explore the anniversary of the day the FF first received their cosmic ray-spawned powers, as memories turn to those early days, when our four intrepid adventurers had to come to grips with how their lives had forever changed. Then, Fabian Nicieza and Steve Rude raffle off the Torch and the Thing at a charity bachelor auction! Up next, Udon (X-MEN: EVOLUTION) explores the question of what gift you get for the couple who has everything! And if that's not enough, Pacheco and Jeph Loeb join forces on a tale that illustrates exactly how the Fantastic Four comic makes its way from their minds to your hands every month!¬†
name: Anniversary

description: Selina Kyle makes her triumphant return as Catwoman, in a stylish new ongoing series written by Ed Brubaker (BATMAN) and illustrated by Darwyn Cooke (BATMAN: EGO) and Mike Allred (Madman). A serial killer is racking up bodies in her old haunts, taking her back to a life she thought she'd left behind permanently.
name: Anodyne, Part One

description: The Feline Fatale's new series continues! Catwoman investigates a string of serial murders down in the slums, leading her into the heart of the Gotham Police Department and an encounter with a face from her past (which should be quite familiar to longtime Catwoman fans). Catwoman may have overcome her recent struggles, but is she really ready for what's waiting for her in the dank streets of Gotham? ¬† ¬†
name: Anodyne, Part Two

description: Selina's on the trail of a serial killer, ¬†one who's targeting women of the night. Unable to track him down through conventional Catwoman- means, and with the police less than successful on the matter, Selina goes undercover to flush out the killer. Meanwhile, Dr. Leslie Thompkins has a very disturbing experience, and Holly helps out Catwoman on a job in a way only Holly can! ¬† ¬†
name: Anodyne, Part Three

description: It's the climactic finish to the strangest case in Catwoman's career. Catwoman finds herself face-to-face with the serial killer she's been pursuing, but he's like nothing she's ever seen in her adventurous life! A battle royale ensues, as Catwoman must take one heck of a drastic measure to stop the threat, ¬†and save her own life! ¬† ¬†
name: Anodyne, Part Four

description:
The new art team of Brad Rader & Cameron Stewart hops aboard as Selina and Holly step into a new mystery! Slam Bradley, the man who led readers to the missing Selina Kyle in DETECTIVE COMICS, returns! While Catwoman is investigating a drug ring involving local children, Slam is on the trail of some corrupt cops. So what do the two cases have to do with one another? Considering this is Gotham, you do the math.

Slam Bradley returns. Catwoman is investigating a drug ring involving local children, while Slam is on the trail of some corrupt cops.
name: Trickle Down Theory

description: A new arc begins as the spotlight shifts to Holly, her personal life, and a mission she takes on for Catwoman. There are some crooked cops running loose in Gotham, and Holly's going to try and get to the bottom of things. But she takes her investigation too far, and even Catwoman can't intervene in time.
name: Disguises, Part One

description: Selina's closest friend and confidant, Holly, has gotten herself into life-threatening danger. Catwoman is racing to the scene, but will she make it in time? Meanwhile, Detective Allen (from the Batman books) is drawn into the corrupt cop conspiracy, and Slam Bradley continues his investigation the way only he can...in his boxers!
name: Disguises, Part Two

description: A DC FULL COVERAGE! entry-point issue! The Doom Patrol is out of work...and it's only their third issue! But even being unemployed doesn't stop them from getting into trouble, or participating in the most peculiar fight scene in recent memory¬†, with the villain known as GOMZ!
name: Grudge Match

description: Meet the new, new Doom Patrol?!? When Robotman and the rest of the team quit, Doom Patrol boss Thayer Jost hires brand-new members to fill the team's roster. But can either team stop the thefts of the mysterious Tycho?
name: Blink... And It's Gone!

description: Forget the Doom Patrol, this is where the Doom Force takes its place in the super-hero-team pantheon. But even though Robotman and the gang are still out there fighting crime, it'll take the combined might of both the Force and the new new Doom Patrol (Metamorpho, Elongated Man, Dr. Light, and Beast Boy) to even challenge the might of Master Chinese demon Nao Yut and his six demon pals!
name: Fade

description: After all the craziness of the last couple of issues, Robotman, the D.P.'s fearless leader, is gone. Now it's up to the rest of the Doom Patrol, if they can get their act together, to try to track him down. Either that, or lay his soul to rest for good!
name: Dead?

description: The search for the earthly remains of Robotman is on, will a startling discovery in the Smoky Mountains leads to the creation of the most outrageous incarnation of Cliff Steele ever?
name: O, Captain! My Captain...

description: A new Robotman comes to grips with the people who brought him back from the "dead," and the freak named Ava reveals a whole new side of herself. Plus the most unexpected story conclusion in the new DOOM PATROL's (seven issue) history!
name: But When I Wake...

description: Once upon a time, the man known as Cliff Steele lost his mind. Now, as Robotman, he's trying to figure out what happened to the rest of him in the years before he got it back. The answers will astound him...and just might cause him to lose his mind one final time.
name: ...My Dreams Have Lied

description: Just when the Doom Patrol thought it was safe to get back to the work of being the world's strangest super-hero team, comes the murderous mystery of the Black Vulture! All this, plus giant worms and...Amazo?!?
name: Asphalt and Good Intentions

description: Just when they thought they'd seen it all...the Doom Patrol goes to Hell. Honest! We swear! (Or at least, it really, really looks that way...). Question is...how are they going to get themselves out?
name: Private Hell

description: The Patrol battles the demon Raum in hell for the souls of thousands of innocents...not to mention themselves! And the team finds unlikely allies in its battle, as well as a shocking revelation or two about their own immortal essences!
name: South of Heaven

description: A new ongoing series from famed writer/artist John Byrne debuts! They've been poked and prodded by scientists, wired into deadly simulations that have cost some of them their very lives. But now these "lab rats" are about to face even greater dangers as they leave their lab behind and face the mysterious threats that fill the DC Universe. ¬†
name: Game Space

description: One of the students has already been killed during a "vacation" to a fairy-tale-themed amusement park, but the troubles are just beginning for the Rats. The secrets behind this strange place, one teeming with bio-engineered threats not limited to living, breathing dragons, may cost even more lives as our heroes try to shut it down for good! ¬†
name: Here There Be Dragons

description: Part 1 of a 3-part time-travel adventure that brings the Rats face-to-face with the Man of Steel! Launched fifty years into the future, the Lab Rats discover a devastated Metropolis...and a mystery only an elderly Jimmy Olsen may be able to solve. But will discovering the source of Metropolis's troubles enable the Rats to return to the present? Also: Who is this future city's mysterious master? And why does he harbor so much hatred for Superman? ¬†
name: Tomorrow Was A Long Time Ago

description: Part 2 of a 3-part time-travel adventure brings the Rats' face-to-face with Superman! The Lab Rats begin to piece together what caused Superman to disappear from Metropolis some fifty years earlier. But will they be able to determine how his absence caused the city's downfall? And will a new, even greater danger, one that threatens all the Earth, make it a moot point? ¬†
name: The Man Of Tomorrow

description: The conclusion of the Rats‚Äô time-travel adventure guest-starring Superman! Catapulted fifty years into the future, the Lab Rats face an alien invasion that may spell the end of the world! Is it possible that their journey through time is somehow responsible for dooming the Earth?
name: Shout Down the Sky

description: Adaptation of Charles Dickens' cautionary tale of a miser, Ebenezer Scrooge, who is visited on Christmas Eve by the ghost of his late partner, Jacob Marley, now condemned to eternal damnation for his life of greed, and then by three ghosts, Christmas Past, Present and Future, who remind him of the man he was in his youth, show him the examples of his good-hearted staff and family in the present and warn him of his imminent death, dying alone, hated and despised, should he not mend his ways.
name: A Christmas Carol
